    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, complete with individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and an M-Variable differential lock. Crucially, the rod bearings have been addressed, and the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates to maintain structural integrity against torque-induced stress. The suspension geometry remains true, providing the precise turn-in and communicative hydraulic steering feedback characteristic of this chassis. While showing honest wear consistent with its age, the mechanical vitals are robust, the cooling system has been refreshed, and the engine pulls strongly to its 8,000 RPM redline.",
      "price": 31500.0,
